						<div class="postbody">Use a debugger is all I can say. Simply by setting a breakpoint in get() (and maybe set()) you should be able to find out if the values propagate properly to the game code. If that doesn't solve the problem, then I'd start stepping through the 6502 emulation code (again, in a debugger) while looking at the disassembly of the Donkey Kong controller reading code. It's probably a loop gathering the 8 controller bits in the accumulator. You can fairly easily verify what value it ends up with.</div>

					
