						<div class="postbody">@Rainwarrior , is there any documnentation on what addresses would have open bus behavior on the cpu data bus?<br /><br />And let me clarify, the value that will be returned on $4016 should be based on how it was addressed.  Since most control pad read loops use absolute addressing, that's why the bits 7 - 4 will be set with 010, since it's the bits in the high byte of val 0x4016.  Correct?  The only way it'd be different is if it was addressed differently.<br /><br />TD</div>

